pgTitle: List of National Monuments of the United States

rows.text: Delaware was the first state to ratify the Constitution, and this monument preserves Dover Green, the New Castle Court House complex, and the Woodlawn property. These sites commemorate Delaware's early settlement, colonial period, and ratification of the Constitution. Delaware is the last state or territory have a NPS unit.
Fort Ord was an Army post from 1917 to 1994. It now has recreational trails and various wildlife.

Poverty Point is a prehistoric archeological site that dates from between 1650 and 700BC and consisting of six earthen rings and seven mounds. The diameter of the outside ridge is miles (km), and the largest mound rises feet (m).

Prehistoric Trackways contains fossilized footprints of numerous Paleozoic amphibians, reptiles, and insects, as well as fossilized plants and petrified wood dating back approximately 280 million years. (Public Law No. 111-11)
